So I am visiting the area, saw ads on college games and thought I'd order a pizza. Called at and waited about 10-15 rings before phone picked up, immediately told to hold - 3 1/2 minutes later, the person takes my order for pick-up, told 20-25 minutes. I show up at exactly 25 minutes and am told the pie is still in the oven, it will be another 5 minutes. 15 minutes goes by and I ask where is my pie - the young lady says it will be 5 minutes, I tell her I've now been here for over 15 minutes past when my pie was supposed to be ready. Another 5 minutes and the manager finally comes over and says there was a mistake and somebody else took my pie, it will be ready in about 5 more minutes. After waiting another 5 minutes, 25 minutes from when I walked in the door I get my pie. FYI, another gentleman waited for the 25-30 minutes for his order as they screwed his up as well. Pie tastes good but service SUCKED!! To top it off, an hour and 10 minutes after I ordered the pie - a delivery person calls me up and say he can't find my address - that was because I called for pick up not delivery and hence that is where the original pie went. My first and last experience EVER for Papa John's. You can put fancy offers on TV but get your frickin house in order will you.
